title: Taxi damaged by wall blown down by Storm Doris | Granada
text:
A taxi has been damaged after Storm Doris blew down a wall.
The cab is buried under a pile of bricks The cab was parked on St Helens road in Bolton, and left buried under a pile of bricks after the gable end of a property collapsed.
The vehicle was parked off St Helens Road Last updated Thu 23 Feb 2017 Read more 26 updates Storm Doris batters North West Weather
